# 3. せめて、私は

Saki: Come on, Ichi! Let's go find Hona and Shiho!
Ichika: Saki... Actually...
Saki: Hmm? What is it?
Ichika: I-It's just that...lunch break is too short to go over for a chat! We wouldn't have time to eat our lunch.
Saki: We can talk while eating. Come on, let's go!
Ichika: Uhm... Okay, sure...
Ichika: (I should explain the situation to her...)
Ichika: (On the other hand, Saki being back might change things between Honami, Shiho, and me...)
Saki: Look, she's over there! Shiho!
Shiho: Saki?! What are you doing here?
Saki: Teehee! Surprised to see me? I've been discharged from the hospital and, from today, I'm back at school!
Shiho: Oh, really? That's good. .....
Saki: Huh? Shiho, is something wrong?
Honami: No way... Saki?!
Saki: Hona! It's been ages! I just came back to school from today!
Honami: I didn't know you were coming back! That's really great news.
Honami: I, um... I have to go now. Sorry.
Saki: Oh, you do?
Honami: Um...
Shiho: My next lesson's in a different classroom, so I've got to go now too.
Saki: What's the hurry? I thought we could have lunch together!
Honami: I... I already promised a friend I'd meet her for lunch. You take care, Saki.
Saki: Hona, but... Gosh, she seemed in a real rush.
Ichika: .....
Saki: What's up with those two...
Ichika: They're probably just really busy. It gets like this in high school.
Ichika: A lot of things are... different now.
Saki: .....
Saki: I guess so... Everyone wants to get the most out of their high school life.
Saki: That's what I should be doing as well! You only live once!
Saki: Thanks for coming with, Ichi!
Ichika: No problem.
Ichika: (Nothing's going to change, is it...)
Honami's Classmate A: Let's walk home together, Honami!
Honami: Okay.
Honami's Classmate B: Did you hear? The class next door got a new student today.
Honami's Classmate A: Ah, yeah, that girl with dyed hair. Didn't you talk to her at lunch break, Honami?
Honami: Y-Yes. We used to go to the same school.
Honami's Classmate A: So you already knew her. I heard she was ill and just recovered enough to come back to school?
Honami: That's right. I didn't know she was coming back today. It was something of a shock for me to see her.
Honami's Classmate B: It was nice of her to remember you and come say hi.
Honami: Yes... She's very kind, and always cheerful.
Shiho: .....
Honami's Classmate A: Oh, are you going home now, Hinomori?
Shiho: Why, you need something?
Honami's Classmate A: Uh... No, I was just asking.
Shiho: I see. Well then, bye.
Honami: .....
Honami's Classmate B: She's kind of cold and unapproachable.
Honami's Classmate A: Yeah. I find her kind of difficult to talk to too. I heard she's in a band, so I'm guessing that thing she was carrying was a guitar?
Honami: It's a bass guitar.
Honami's Classmate A: You can tell?
Honami: I, um...heard someone mention it.
Honami's Classmate B: Apparently, she's always been like this. A girl who was in the same class as her in junior high told me.
Honami's Classmate B: She gets hostile when anyone tries to make friends with her.
Honami: .....
Honami's Classmate A: Really? Maybe she prefers to be alone.
Honami: Hey, um...
Honami's Classmate B: What's up?
Honami: I was thinking of going to the bookstore on the way home. Want to come with me?
Honami's Classmate B: Sure, sounds good!
Honami: Great! Oh, and by the way...
